<subSubSection id="0C00F264AC3EA6A153550BFAC582A61C" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" type="recognition and notes">
<paragraph id="EE21FE0A14CB842D4E83E8D67A6012BF" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">Recognition and notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F992BEB395C6D3436777E87732AC9B03" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">
<taxonomicName id="07E7692AAB1EC7EC7FE0BCEDA31DD562" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Connaraceae" genus="Rourea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Rourea martiana" order="Oxalidales" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="martiana">
<emphasis id="B7F4694A74A969AD6E1A2181E75FFD00" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">Rourea martiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is recognised by possessing glandular trichomes, a relatively long-peduncle (0.9-3.8 cm) and a short pedicel (ca 2 mm long).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="15FA7C87C26FB08CCAAA0CD792B92FF1" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">
<bibRefCitation id="743F286FCB8DF57D962E0D6101968189" author="Baker, JG" editor="Martius, CFP von" journalOrPublisher="2. R. Oldenbourg, Munich &amp; Leipzig" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" pagination="172 - 196" refId="B4" refString="Baker, JG, 1871. Connaraceae. In: Martius, CFP von, Ed., Flora Brasiliensis 14, pt. 2. R. Oldenbourg, Munich &amp; Leipzig: 172 - 196" title="Connaraceae." volumeTitle="Flora Brasiliensis 14, pt." year="1871">Baker (1871)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName id="91B00469A2A7B5C58162848B5E31EEFD" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Connaraceae" genus="Rourea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Rourea martiana" order="Oxalidales" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="martiana">
<emphasis id="AEFFF566F0B6B4D2A8529D2B48BFBEA3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">Rourea martiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on the collections of Martius 1675 and Warming 1849, without mentioning the type; the former is only deposited in M, while the latter is deposited in C, GH and K. 
<bibRefCitation id="ADFBED5E60BAE894223F1112DCC40EA7" author="Schellenberg, G" editor="Engler, A" journalOrPublisher="W. Engelmann, Leipzig" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" pagination="1 - 326" refId="B25" refString="Schellenberg, G, 1938. Connaraceae. In: Engler, A, Ed., Das Pflanzenreich IV (127) (Heft 103). W. Engelmann, Leipzig: 1 - 326" title="Connaraceae." volumeTitle="Das Pflanzenreich IV (127) (Heft 103)." year="1938">Schellenberg (1938)</bibRefCitation>
inadvertently indicated the lectotype of 
<taxonomicName id="BFDFE66387393E844D639949CECF40A4" family="Connaraceae" genus="R." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="R. martiana" order="Oxalidales" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" rank="species" species="martiana">
<emphasis id="B907BDCCF5626E7E3EC91646AF06C7BE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">R. martiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Martius 1675) and described 
<taxonomicName id="C8AC22E37F765947D0ECFCDD6EC02C05" family="Connaraceae" genus="R." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="R. cnestidifolia" order="Oxalidales" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" rank="species" species="cnestidifolia">
<emphasis id="1CBC301B7891CC805FDDBAC4432D5E41" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">R. cnestidifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, citing Warming 1849 as paratype. 
<bibRefCitation id="2A2DE1EE6C2E212B66D226FB707A17B6" author="Forero, E" journalOrPublisher="Memoirs of the New York Botanical Garden" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" pagination="1 - 119" refId="B10" refString="Forero, E, 1976. A revision of the American species of Rourea subgenus Rourea (Connaraceae). Memoirs of the New York Botanical Garden 26 (1): 1 - 119" title="A revision of the American species of Rourea subgenus Rourea (Connaraceae)." volume="26" year="1976">Forero (1976)</bibRefCitation>
followed 
<normalizedToken id="F118E53BBE3FB0BBC846BCD8F4EE5BEE" originalValue="Schellenberg’s">Schellenberg's</normalizedToken>
position, although he called the specimen Martius 1675 holotype of 
<taxonomicName id="F843F96A902E0899A59BED8C47E4F132" family="Connaraceae" genus="R." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="R. martiana" order="Oxalidales" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" rank="species" species="martiana">
<emphasis id="295F445543030DBBA172CAD91E8C2094" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">R. martiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and selected Warming 1849 from K as lectotype of 
<taxonomicName id="DAFBD3C23653D81E725294A184404F95" family="Connaraceae" genus="R." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="R. cnestidifolia" order="Oxalidales" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" rank="species" species="cnestidifolia">
<emphasis id="41A17E8536BD2F910EE7A294E18AF9F1" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">R. cnestidifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
after the holotype from B (Sellow s. n.) was considered missing. 
<bibRefCitation id="68BDE4DF38A20BE9DCBBD4768733377E" author="Baker, JG" editor="Martius, CFP von" journalOrPublisher="2. R. Oldenbourg, Munich &amp; Leipzig" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" pagination="172 - 196" refId="B4" refString="Baker, JG, 1871. Connaraceae. In: Martius, CFP von, Ed., Flora Brasiliensis 14, pt. 2. R. Oldenbourg, Munich &amp; Leipzig: 172 - 196" title="Connaraceae." volumeTitle="Flora Brasiliensis 14, pt." year="1871">Baker (1871)</bibRefCitation>
indeed described 
<taxonomicName id="E339DCD7CEA8E7E65469B986F7D1C447" family="Connaraceae" genus="R." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="R. martiana" order="Oxalidales" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" rank="species" species="martiana">
<emphasis id="EB0C9EB7C1BD1BAD0C515F38079551EB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">R. martiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on two specimens that should be treated as different taxa, so 
<bibRefCitation id="D5570704CEBF74426F0808A888DA1654" author="Schellenberg, G" editor="Engler, A" journalOrPublisher="W. Engelmann, Leipzig" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" pagination="1 - 326" refId="B25" refString="Schellenberg, G, 1938. Connaraceae. In: Engler, A, Ed., Das Pflanzenreich IV (127) (Heft 103). W. Engelmann, Leipzig: 1 - 326" title="Connaraceae." volumeTitle="Das Pflanzenreich IV (127) (Heft 103)." year="1938">Schellenberg (1938)</bibRefCitation>
was right in selecting a type for 
<taxonomicName id="174A65EE5619BAB6CC281DD3D81F8D7A" family="Connaraceae" genus="R." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="R. martiana" order="Oxalidales" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" rank="species" species="martiana">
<emphasis id="92FAC0FF944CA72CD0545465A133C4D4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">R. martiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and describing 
<taxonomicName id="35AF72E02B9262D817104059D138A3C6" family="Connaraceae" genus="R." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="R. cnestidifolia" order="Oxalidales" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" rank="species" species="cnestidifolia">
<emphasis id="3A9163AE07B8D07F53A2AADF76E8D14F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">R. cnestidifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The former differs by the middle and apical leaflets up to 4 cm long with usually rounded apex, while in the latter, leaflets are longer than 4 cm with obtuse, acute or narrowly rounded apex.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="51B05DEE862AE0A48E5E3A02B95583BF" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">
After fixing the application of 
<taxonomicName id="958B550241209C5DAC3F4EF97205C658" family="Connaraceae" genus="R." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="R. martiana" order="Oxalidales" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" rank="species" species="martiana">
<emphasis id="9B61776D7BD33734006E9209B70F2BE1" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">R. martiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to Martius 1675, however, both 
<bibRefCitation id="AB9C63A2734FF17438D10634F5D5349A" author="Schellenberg, G" editor="Engler, A" journalOrPublisher="W. Engelmann, Leipzig" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" pagination="1 - 326" refId="B25" refString="Schellenberg, G, 1938. Connaraceae. In: Engler, A, Ed., Das Pflanzenreich IV (127) (Heft 103). W. Engelmann, Leipzig: 1 - 326" title="Connaraceae." volumeTitle="Das Pflanzenreich IV (127) (Heft 103)." year="1938">Schellenberg (1938)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="1EDC4E8E4F1C5FEF1D9294459CDF31D1" author="Forero, E" journalOrPublisher="Memoirs of the New York Botanical Garden" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" pagination="1 - 119" refId="B10" refString="Forero, E, 1976. A revision of the American species of Rourea subgenus Rourea (Connaraceae). Memoirs of the New York Botanical Garden 26 (1): 1 - 119" title="A revision of the American species of Rourea subgenus Rourea (Connaraceae)." volume="26" year="1976">Forero (1976</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="C0BF45C670DEEAE950CB0127C05AE852" author="Forero, E" journalOrPublisher="Memoirs of the New York Botanical Garden" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" refId="B11" refString="Forero, E, 1983. Connaraceae. Flora Neotropica Monograph 36. New York Botanical Garden Press, New York, 1-208." title="Connaraceae. Flora Neotropica Monograph 36. New York Botanical Garden Press, New York, 1 - 208." year="1983">1983</bibRefCitation>
) seem to have confused the identity of the species and grouped specimens morphologically distinct and geographically isolated. The type of 
<taxonomicName id="EEC18D2C858CA0AFB684398A5346A28E" family="Connaraceae" genus="R." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="R. martiana" order="Oxalidales" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" rank="species" species="martiana">
<emphasis id="06AE306B1AFFC3DC52EFEDEBC456DA31" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">R. martiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was collected in Minas Gerais and, although without a precise location, this specimen matches those collected in central and northeast of the state and south-western Bahia, which are characterised by leaves 9-15-foliolate and a short pedicel (ca. 2 mm long). The specimens, here treated under a new species (
<taxonomicName id="4DDBD1ADE96F444FE72A201C9E204FB8" family="Connaraceae" genus="R." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="R. diamantina" order="Oxalidales" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" rank="species" species="diamantina">
<emphasis id="1B1B0F2D6FFCA0E0299B6C72FBB8D0C4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">R. diamantina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) - but identified as 
<taxonomicName id="3721EE1AA69223FC5A663850FE8FB7F5" family="Connaraceae" genus="R." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="R. martiana" order="Oxalidales" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" rank="species" species="martiana">
<emphasis id="7FAB99BC5659B4EA7927DD9274D13FFD" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">R. martiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="0DC61332CADE422555AA315A44366923" author="Schellenberg, G" editor="Engler, A" journalOrPublisher="W. Engelmann, Leipzig" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" pagination="1 - 326" refId="B25" refString="Schellenberg, G, 1938. Connaraceae. In: Engler, A, Ed., Das Pflanzenreich IV (127) (Heft 103). W. Engelmann, Leipzig: 1 - 326" title="Connaraceae." volumeTitle="Das Pflanzenreich IV (127) (Heft 103)." year="1938">Schellenberg (1938)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="2B768B14B3976484657CC2DC67A0B293" author="Forero, E" journalOrPublisher="Memoirs of the New York Botanical Garden" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" pagination="1 - 119" refId="B10" refString="Forero, E, 1976. A revision of the American species of Rourea subgenus Rourea (Connaraceae). Memoirs of the New York Botanical Garden 26 (1): 1 - 119" title="A revision of the American species of Rourea subgenus Rourea (Connaraceae)." volume="26" year="1976">Forero (1976</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="87ACCA4D85D2B076D17F135A9CD3D8FE" author="Forero, E" journalOrPublisher="Memoirs of the New York Botanical Garden" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" refId="B11" refString="Forero, E, 1983. Connaraceae. Flora Neotropica Monograph 36. New York Botanical Garden Press, New York, 1-208." title="Connaraceae. Flora Neotropica Monograph 36. New York Botanical Garden Press, New York, 1 - 208." year="1983">1983</bibRefCitation>
) - are restricted to central Bahia and characterised by leaves 5-9(-13)-foliolate and a longer pedicel (5-13 mm long). Additionally, leaflets in 
<taxonomicName id="C588BB5A503FD89973F9806C791D7D9B" family="Connaraceae" genus="R." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="R. martiana" order="Oxalidales" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" rank="species" species="martiana">
<emphasis id="E87C77D7F6D7380D37A7A195F8414377" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">R. martiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
become slightly larger towards the apex and are usually oblong or narrowly elliptic with rounded apex (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="59C9FF9764F95724D3CAB838CBB5DB06" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Leaves in Rourea subgen. R. sect. Multifoliolatae: A R. discolor B R. martiana C R. tenuis D R. cnestidifolia." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.169.54297.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/484418" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">1B</figureCitation>
), whereas in 
<taxonomicName id="C64CC0A56FCD15A919267049A5FE3990" family="Connaraceae" genus="R." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="R. diamantina" order="Oxalidales" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" rank="species" species="diamantina">
<emphasis id="8709FBD67F2FD9D8F50EB0B65C8C7332" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">R. diamantina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, they become significantly larger towards the apex and are usually narrowly ovate with obtuse or narrowly-rounded apex (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="94972A2F076F19A68A67FF31318DC569" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Rourea diamantina: A flowering branchlet B leaf, abaxial surface C indumentum, leaflet abaxial surface D flower, external view E flower, internal view F stamens G ovary, external view H ovary, internal view and ovules I fruit and seed, external view J seed, external view K sepal indumentum, external view." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.169.54297.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/484424" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">7B</figureCitation>
). Both species are morphologically similar due to the presence of glandular trichomes, leaves and leaflets relatively small and flowers and fruits with similar characteristics. Geographically, these two species are separated by the Chapada Diamantina (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="838A9A01B63FB3E3A7101DF722D4798F" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Geographic distribution of Rourea diamantina (circles) and R. martiana (triangles)." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.169.54297.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/484425" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">8</figureCitation>
), a mountain range located in central Bahia approximately 41,700 km2 long and altitudes up to 2,000 m. They also occur in different environments: 
<taxonomicName id="75C6BAEE49CB436604E032FF318B7C74" family="Connaraceae" genus="R." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="R. martiana" order="Oxalidales" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" rank="species" species="martiana">
<emphasis id="F870A0BC831A54CF7B4295B851EB76BF" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">R. martiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
grows in areas of Cerrado 
<emphasis id="9458853B1537651AAECAD6EA1D75A709" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">s. s.</emphasis>
(occasionally with rocky soils), while 
<taxonomicName id="14D7E1D473A16E03D3C91B22A6B20CEF" family="Connaraceae" genus="R." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="R. diamantina" order="Oxalidales" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" rank="species" species="diamantina">
<emphasis id="D2712781F729B530A0256CDE59A0CBCF" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">R. diamantina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
grows in seasonal forests on Inselbergs.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="95F38113CF2AEB270AD4DD2A6582D05A" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">
The position taken by 
<bibRefCitation id="89A2AAB66205A114E2DB733C7EBE5754" author="Schellenberg, G" editor="Engler, A" journalOrPublisher="W. Engelmann, Leipzig" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" pagination="1 - 326" refId="B25" refString="Schellenberg, G, 1938. Connaraceae. In: Engler, A, Ed., Das Pflanzenreich IV (127) (Heft 103). W. Engelmann, Leipzig: 1 - 326" title="Connaraceae." volumeTitle="Das Pflanzenreich IV (127) (Heft 103)." year="1938">Schellenberg (1938)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="FADC7499ADDD6CFA795C4F4CD42BC7A7" author="Forero, E" journalOrPublisher="Memoirs of the New York Botanical Garden" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" pagination="1 - 119" refId="B10" refString="Forero, E, 1976. A revision of the American species of Rourea subgenus Rourea (Connaraceae). Memoirs of the New York Botanical Garden 26 (1): 1 - 119" title="A revision of the American species of Rourea subgenus Rourea (Connaraceae)." volume="26" year="1976">Forero (1976</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="6BE6112388134F856C8177EAECFD2E57" author="Forero, E" journalOrPublisher="Memoirs of the New York Botanical Garden" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" refId="B11" refString="Forero, E, 1983. Connaraceae. Flora Neotropica Monograph 36. New York Botanical Garden Press, New York, 1-208." title="Connaraceae. Flora Neotropica Monograph 36. New York Botanical Garden Press, New York, 1 - 208." year="1983">1983</bibRefCitation>
) may be explained because the specimens from Minas Gerais were not available at the time. Nevertheless, the disjunct distribution and the morphological differences are consistent enough to recognise 
<taxonomicName id="D23477D6D7C35C1274075544BF96A61B" family="Connaraceae" genus="R." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="R. martiana" order="Oxalidales" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" rank="species" species="martiana">
<emphasis id="7A68247F2E361933D2D8B866EE470F07" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">R. martiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="38E4F8DA7AF80EB7582412417443CB94" family="Connaraceae" genus="R." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="R. diamantina" order="Oxalidales" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" rank="species" species="diamantina">
<emphasis id="BCC7585338FF9DA02FDEF0961EA16E21" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">R. diamantina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as distinct species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="56E8CBA2BB588C889B7187C06CCDCD5A" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">
The type collection from M is composed of two herbarium sheets mounted separately, but one of them (barcode M-0243940) has an original blue label of Martius, whereas the other (barcode M-0243941) has a different label. According to the 
<emphasis id="F4CC8EF2543DBFED17DB559FB8021881" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">Code</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="7FCFD830AE6ABCB8944BBC6080E19173" DOI="https://doi.org/10.12705/Code.2018" author="Turland, NJ" journalOrPublisher="Phytotaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" refId="B28" refString="Turland, NJ, Wiersema, JH, Barrie, FR, Greuter, W, Hawksworth, DL, Herendeen, PS, Knapp, S, Kusber, W-H, Li, D-Z, Marhold, K, May, TW, McNeill, J, Monro, AM, Prado, J, Price, MJ, Smith, GF, 2018. International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017. Regnum Vegetabile 159. Koeltz Botanical Books, Glashuetten. https://doi.org/10.12705/Code.2018" title="International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017. Regnum Vegetabile 159. Koeltz Botanical Books, Glashuetten." url="https://doi.org/10.12705/Code.2018" year="2018">Turland et al. 2018</bibRefCitation>
, Art. 8.3, Ex. 10), these should be regarded as duplicates, so a second step lectotypification is here proposed.
</paragraph>
